  "body": "# Rationale\r\nWe want to differentiate CREATE and CREATE2 opcodes in native tracers. We can do that in JS tracers.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunc (t *noopTracer) CaptureStart(env *vm.EVM, from common.Address, to common.Address, create bool, input []byte, gas uint64, value *big.Int) {\r\n}\r\n```\r\nWe only have a boolean parameter called `create` to indicate if it is CREATE2 or CREATE\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\n\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\nWe want to differentiate CREATE and CREATE2 opcodes and have different handling mechanisms.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nNo\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nYes",
